			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-style: italic">...continued from ^</span>
<br />

<br />

<br />
I come out of my daydream; the sun is shining in my eyes as it sets over the wasteland before me. It’s time to get going. Making sure it’s clear I step out of the protection of the tree line to search for the components I need to reanimate my means of travel.
<br />

<br />
Just as I spy what I need I feel a presence, a shadow just beyond my perception. I look around but see nothing. I will have to be cautious. Though I see nothing I am obviously not alone. A few more steps out into the open and I find what I’m looking for. A bone fragment, partially buried under some loose rock. Kneeling down I brush away some of the dirt and inspect it. I’m lucky; it’s a stallion’s cannon bone. This will do nicely.
<br />
	
<br />
Standing up I take another look around. I still see nothing in any direction, but the presence is still quite strong. I cannot delay anymore. Speaking the runes, I call upon the spirit of the stallion. Within seconds the reanimation is complete and a skeletal stallion stands before me. This mighty beast would have served one of the Unali cavalry well during the war.
<br />
	
<br />
It has most of its skin, though grey and decaying. Patches of bone are visible around the legs where it would have taken slashes from Therali or Etokin swords during the fray. There’s a large pierce wound upon its chest. That most likely would have been the fatal blow from a spear.
<br />
	
<br />
Hopping into the saddle I urge the stallion into a full gallop to the south. What I don’t see is the wispy ground fog that follows us.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
